      "date": "2011-09-02 16:56:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nInstead of changing the whole message to be a CDEBUG(D_INFO), which makes it so nobody will ever see it, whatever OBD_BRW flag is triggering this problem should be added to mask, assuming that it is not exposing some other problem (e.g. mixed read and write pages inone RPC or similar). \n\nI would be ok to make this a CWARN(), and potentially also limit the error to once per mask bit, like:\n\n         static __u32 save_diff;\n         __u32 diff;\n\n         diff = (p1->flags & mask) ^ (p2->flags & mask);\n         if (unlikely(diff && (diff & save_diff == 0))) {\n                 CWARN(...);\n                 save_diff |= diff;\n         }",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
